## 2026-04-04 - Plugin sandbox lacks mutual exclusion for concurrent sync operations
- Added promise-chain mutex (`_syncChain` + `withSyncLock`) in `controller.ts` immediately after `deepInspectEnabled` declaration.
- Wrapped `apply-variables`, `apply-styles`, and `delete-orphan-variables` cases in `withSyncLock()` — these are the only operations that mutate Figma variables/styles. Read-only operations (`read-variables`, `read-styles`, `get-selection`, etc.) bypass the lock intentionally.
- The lock chain absorbs per-operation rejections so a failed sync does not permanently block the queue.

